      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/175/5879",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ : \"كَلِمَتَانِ غَرِيبَتَانِ فَاحْتَمِلُوهُمَا كَلِمَةُ حِكْمَةٍ مِنْ سَفِيهٍ فَاقْبَلُوهَا وَ كَلِمَةُ سَفَهٍ مِنْ حَكِيمٍ فَاغْفِرُوهَا\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5879 - Al-Sakuni narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), from his forefathers, peace be upon them, that the Messenger of Allah (swt), peace and blessings be upon him and his family, said:\n\"Two words are strange, so bear them patiently:\nA word of wisdom from a foolish person - accept it;\nand a foolish word from a wise person - forgive it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
